@mrmaddog0001
He's right, subtitle tracks take almost no space & you can always turn them on or off if you don't like them. They're right there on the DVD, once you upload without them it gets a lot more complicated to get them back.

When doing a DVDrip it's good policy to always either embed or include any subtitle files for speakers of other languages or those (like me) who are hard of hearing after a decade or two working backstage.

@Ryan1755
No luck yet, I'll keep looking so us poor, deaf bastards can understand what's being said without deafening the neighbors.

